Based on French specimens: Savoie, Allevard, Val Pelouse, 1400 m, 7.06.1987. Male (Fig. 2
a-f
): Tergite VI with two small triangular appendices pointing upwards and backwards in side view (Fig. 2b). Tergite VII with non-interrupted anterior margin and wide median bell-shaped membranous area. Tergite VIII with two strong teeth pointing upwards and backwards in side view (Fig. 2a, b, f); teeth sub-rectangular in dorsal view (Fig. 2f). Tergite IX with anterior margin interrupted on nearly half segment width, lateral edges triangular ending in sharp angles near anterior margin. Lateral lobes of paraprocts with a sclerotized hook-shaped expansion turning backwards and extending along distal part of specilla (Fig. 2
c-d
). Specilla straight in ventral and side views (Fig. 2
c-d
), slightly curved at their tip (Fig. 2c). Sternite IX: ventral vesicle racket-shaped (Fig. 2e). Female (Fig. 2g): subgenital plate with two rounded lobes separated by a small rounded lamella; a triangular sclerite placed between the 2 lobes is visible beneath transparent cuticle.
